# Broadcast Traffic Control using SDN (Mininet & POX)

## Objective
The objective of this project is to control broadcast traffic using Software Defined Networking (SDN).

## Tools Used
- Mininet
- POX Controller
- Open vSwitch
- Ubuntu

## Topology
Single switch topology with 3 hosts (h1, h2, h3)

## Steps to Execute

1. Start POX Controller:
   cd ~/pox
   python3 pox.py forwarding.l2_learning

2. Start Mininet:
   sudo mn --topo single,3 --mac --controller remote

3. Test connectivity:
   pingall

4. Apply broadcast blocking:
   sudo ovs-ofctl add-flow s1 "dl_dst=ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff,actions=drop"

5. Verify flow rule:
   sudo ovs-ofctl dump-flows s1

6. Test again:
   pingall

7. Measure throughput:
   h1 iperf -s &
   h2 iperf -c h1

## Result
Broadcast traffic was successfully blocked, causing ARP failure and communication loss.

## Conclusion
SDN allows dynamic control of network traffic using flow rules.

